"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1111253","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-04-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the reply given to the hon. Member for Mid Derbyshire, Pauline Latham, on 19 February 2019 to PQ 220196.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2019-04-15T14:24:51.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1111253/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1111253/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1111253/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-04-10","Canoeing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate he has made of the total length of unmanaged waterways in England to which canoeists have an undisputed right of navigation.","false","Biography information for John Grogan","Keighley","John Grogan","243345"
